<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Indian Armed Forces Subdomains</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            color: #333;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 20px auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        }

        h1, h2 {
            color: #283747; /* Dark grayish blue */
        }

        .subdomain {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .subdomain h3 {
            margin-bottom: 5px;
            color: #566573; /* Slightly lighter grayish blue */
        }

        .subdomain p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .demand, .colleges, .scholarships {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Indian Armed Forces Subdomains</h1>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Indian Army</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>The land-based branch, responsible for ground warfare. It includes infantry, armored corps, artillery, engineers, and signals.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Indian Navy</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>The maritime branch, responsible for protecting India's sea borders. It includes surface warships, submarines, and naval aviation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Indian Air Force (IAF)</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>The aerial warfare branch, responsible for protecting India's airspace. It includes fighter aircraft, transport aircraft, and helicopters.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Indian Coast Guard</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Responsible for maritime law enforcement, search and rescue, and protecting India's maritime interests.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subdomain">
            <h2>Paramilitary Forces</h2>
            <h3>Description:</h3>
            <p>Includes forces like the Border Security Force (BSF), Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF), and others, which assist the armed forces in various internal and external security roles.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="demand">
            <h2>Demand of the Armed Forces in India</h2>
            <p>The demand for the Indian Armed Forces is driven by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Protecting national sovereignty and territorial integrity.</li>
                <li>Addressing external threats and maintaining regional stability.</li>
                <li>Countering terrorism and internal security challenges.</li>
                <li>Providing humanitarian assistance and disaster relief.</li>
                <li>Contributing to international peacekeeping missions.</li>
                <li>Technological advancements requiring skilled personnel.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="colleges">
            <h2>Colleges for Armed Forces</h2>
            <p>Key institutions for training and education include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>National Defence Academy (NDA), Khadakwasla</li>
                <li>Indian Military Academy (IMA), Dehradun</li>
                <li>Officers Training Academy (OTA), Chennai and Gaya</li>
                <li>Naval Academy, Ezhimala</li>
                <li>Air Force Academy, Dundigal</li>
                <li>Military Engineering College (CME), Pune</li>
                <li>Armed Forces Medical College (AFMC), Pune</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="scholarships">
            <h2>Scholarships for Armed Forces</h2>
            <p>Scholarships and financial assistance often involve:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Government-funded training and education at academies.</li>
                <li>Stipends and allowances during training periods.</li>
                <li>Educational concessions for children of armed forces personnel.</li>
                <li>Ex-servicemen welfare schemes providing financial aid.</li>
                <li>Scholarships from private organizations for dependents of service members.</li>
                <li>Specific scholarships for students joining AFMC.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Specific scholarship details vary and should be confirmed with the respective institutions or government websites.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>